[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = OkRegistrator","category":"page"},{"location":"#OkRegistrator","page":"Home","title":"OkRegistrator","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for OkRegistrator.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [OkRegistrator]","category":"page"},{"location":"#OkRegistrator.baseexactexpr-Tuple{Any}","page":"Home","title":"OkRegistrator.baseexactexpr","text":"baseexactexpr(regrepo) returns expression matching exactly the basename of regrepo.\n\nExample\n\nexpr = OkRegistrator.baseexactexpr(\".julia/dev/OkRegistry\")\noccursin(expr, \"OkRegistry\")\n\n# output\n\ntrue\n\noccursin(expr, \"NotOkRegistry\")\n\n# output\n\nfalse\n\noccursin(expr, \"NotOkAtRegistryAll\")\n\n# output\n\nfalse\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#OkRegistrator.folderlist-Tuple{Any}","page":"Home","title":"OkRegistrator.folderlist","text":"folderlist(dir; join=true) return the list of folder but no subfolder under dir. This function uses walkdir.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#OkRegistrator.folderlist-Tuple{Regex, Any}","page":"Home","title":"OkRegistrator.folderlist","text":"folderlist(expr::Regex, dir; join=true) returns a vector of paths who match expr.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#OkRegistrator.folderlist-Tuple{}","page":"Home","title":"OkRegistrator.folderlist","text":"folderlist(;kwargs...) returns results in the current directory (pwd)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#OkRegistrator.isprerelease-Tuple{Any}","page":"Home","title":"OkRegistrator.isprerelease","text":"Given the package directory pkgpath, isprerelease(pkgpath) returns true if there is nothing left after matching r\"(\\d+.?)+\". Use this to check whether to registor a version or not.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#OkRegistrator.isprerelease-Tuple{VersionNumber}","page":"Home","title":"OkRegistrator.isprerelease","text":"isprerelease(ver::VersionNumber)\n\nExample\n\nisprerelease(v\"0.99.5\")\n\n# output\n\nfalse\n\nisprerelease(v\"0.99.5-DEV\")\n\n# output\n\ntrue\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#OkRegistrator.okciregister-Tuple{Any}","page":"Home","title":"OkRegistrator.okciregister","text":"Given the directory of your local registry okregpath, okciregister(okregpath) attempts to register all pacakges (folders) under dirname(okregpath).\n\nThis is used in the CI. See also the template register.yml in OkPkgTemplates.jl.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#OkRegistrator.tryregisterat-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"OkRegistrator.tryregisterat","text":"tryregisterat(pkgpath, regpath) try to register package at pkgpath to local registry at regpath. If failed, it raises warnings and returns iserrored = true.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
